The paper deals with secure distributed graph algorithms, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses information-theoretic security, which is a topic in Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). The use of private neighborhood trees involves combinatorial structures, which is a topic in Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses privacy concerns, which is a topic in Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper introduces a new compiler for secure distributed graph algorithms, which is a topic in Computational Complexity (cs.CC).
